<section id=3D"S5.SS3" class=3D"ltx_subsection">
<h3 class=3D"ltx_title ltx_title_subsection">
<span class=3D"ltx_tag ltx_tag_subsection">5.3. </span><span id=3D"S5.SS3.2=
.1" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_bold">RQ3: Ablation Study on Knowledge Quali=
ty</span>
</h3>

<div id=3D"S5.SS3.p1" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S5.SS3.p1.1" class=3D"ltx_p">While RQ1 and RQ2 show that distillin=
g knowledge from a mixture of experts improves predictive performance and a=
dversarial robustness, it is unclear whether these gains stem from higher-q=
uality aggregated knowledge. To assess whether the benefits of <span id=3D"=
S5.SS3.p1.1.1" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MoEKD</span> persist unde=
r aggressive compression, we conduct an ablation study using ultra-compact =
CodeBERT-based student models of approximately 2 MB and 1.6 MB. The archite=
cture of these models is selected from the Pareto-optimal sets produced by =
<span id=3D"S5.SS3.p1.1.2" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Compressor</s=
pan> and <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p1.1.3" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">AVAT=
AR</span>.</p>
</div>
<div id=3D"S5.SS3.p2" class=3D"ltx_para">
<p id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1" class=3D"ltx_p"><span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1.1" class=3D"l=
tx_text ltx_font_bold">Accuracy under reduced model capacity: </span>
Table <a href=3D"https://arxiv.org/html/2603.13213v1#S5.T3" title=3D"Table =
3 =E2=80=A3 5.3. RQ3: Ablation Study on Knowledge Quality =E2=80=A3 5. Eval=
uation Results =E2=80=A3 Leveraging Mixture of Experts (MoE) to Improve Kno=
wledge Distillation for Language Models of Code" class=3D"ltx_ref"><span cl=
ass=3D"ltx_text ltx_ref_tag">3</span></a> shows that <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.=
1.2" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MoEKD</span> maintains its performa=
nce gains even with aggressive model compression, demonstrating the strengt=
h of aggregated expert knowledge. For both <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1.3" class=
=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">Compressor</span> and <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1=
.4" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">AVATAR</span> architectures, <span i=
d=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1.5" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MoEKD</span> produce=
s student models of 1.6 MB and 2 MB that consistently outperform the 3 MB s=
ingle-teacher baselines. In the <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1.6" class=3D"ltx_tex=
t ltx_font_italic">Compressor</span> architecture, <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1.=
7" class=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MoEKD</span> increases accuracy from =
0.54 to 0.59 and 0.60 at 1.6 MB and 2 MB, respectively, despite the smaller=
 model size. Similarly, for <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1.8" class=3D"ltx_text lt=
x_font_italic">AVATAR</span>-based students, <span id=3D"S5.SS3.p2.1.9" cla=
ss=3D"ltx_text ltx_font_italic">MoEKD</span> achieves accuracies of 0.60 an=
d 0.61 at 1.6 MB and 2 MB, exceeding the 3 MB single-teacher baseline accur=
acy of 0.57.</p>
</div>
